Ecomorph is a compositing manager for [Moksha](http://mokshadesktop.org). 
It consists of the ecomorph module for Moksha and [ecomp](https://github.com/JeffHoogland/ecomp).

1. install [Moksha](https://github.com/JeffHoogland/moksha)
2. install [ecomp](https://github.com/JeffHoogland/ecomp)
3. install ecomorph module.. from there where this REAME file comes from 
4. load ecomorph module
5. in main menu -> settings choose ecomorph
6. click 'start ecomp'
7. activate ecomorph mode
8. click apply

9. if everything works well you can log out 
   and start ecomorph.sh + ecomorph-mode
   via "ecomorph - e17 session"

10. configure bindings for actions with e's mouse-, key- and edge-bindings 
   dialogs.

Required packages for building on debian/ubuntu/Bodhi:
 git-core automake intltool libtool 
 xorg-dev libjpeg62-dev libpng12-dev 
 librsvg2-dev libgl1-mesa-dev 
 libglu1-mesa-dev libxml2-dev 
 libxslt1 libxslt1-dev libdbus-1-dev 
